---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { site } from '../data/site';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service"
  description="Terms of Service for Accountium — the rules and conditions for using our platform."
>
  <section class="page-hero section-sm" aria-label="Terms of Service">
    <div class="container page-hero-inner">
      <p class="section-label">Legal</p>
      <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="page-subline">
        Last updated: March 7, 2026
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="terms-section section-sm">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="feat-divider" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      <div class="prose glass-card">

        <h2>1. Agreement to Terms</h2>
        <p>
          By accessing or using the Accountium platform at <strong>{site.url}</strong> or any associated
          mobile or desktop application (collectively, the "Service"), you agree to be bound by these
          Terms of Service ("Terms"). If you do not agree, do not use the Service.
        </p>
        <p>
          These Terms apply to all users, including individuals, businesses, and organizations that
          access the Service on behalf of a company.
        </p>

        <h2>2. Eligibility</h2>
        <p>
          You must be at least 18 years old and legally capable of entering into a binding contract to
          use the Service. By using Accountium, you represent and warrant that you meet these requirements.
          If you are using the Service on behalf of a business, you represent that you have the authority
          to bind that business to these Terms.
        </p>

        <h2>3. Account Registration</h2>
        <p>
          To access most features, you must create an account. You agree to:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Provide accurate, complete, and current information during registration.</li>
          <li>Keep your login credentials confidential and not share them with others.</li>
          <li>Notify us immediately at <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a> if you suspect unauthorized access to your account.</li>
          <li>Accept responsibility for all activity that occurs under your account.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. Subscription and Payment</h2>
        <h3>4.1 Plans and billing</h3>
        <p>
          Accountium offers paid subscription plans. By selecting a plan, you authorize us to charge
          your chosen payment method on a recurring basis (monthly or annually, depending on your
          selection). All fees are in Canadian dollars unless otherwise stated.
        </p>
        <h3>4.2 Free trial</h3>
        <p>
          We may offer a free trial period. At the end of the trial, your account will automatically
          convert to a paid plan unless you cancel before the trial expires.
        </p>
        <h3>4.3 Refunds</h3>
        <p>
          All payments are non-refundable except where required by applicable law. If you believe a
          charge was made in error, contact us within 14 days of the charge.
        </p>
        <h3>4.4 Price changes</h3>
        <p>
          We reserve the right to change subscription pricing. We will provide at least 30 days'
          notice before any price change takes effect for existing subscribers.
        </p>

        <h2>5. Acceptable Use</h2>
        <p>You agree not to use the Service to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Violate any applicable law or regulation.</li>
          <li>Process, store, or transmit fraudulent or illegal financial data.</li>
          <li>Upload malicious code, viruses, or any harmful software.</li>
          <li>Attempt to gain unauthorized access to any part of the Service or its infrastructure.</li>
          <li>Scrape, reverse-engineer, or copy any portion of the Service without our written consent.</li>
          <li>Use the Service to provide competing services to third parties without prior written agreement.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>6. Your Data</h2>
        <p>
          You retain ownership of all financial data, files, and content you upload or create within
          the Service ("Your Data"). By using the Service, you grant Accountium a limited, non-exclusive
          license to store, process, and display Your Data solely to provide the Service to you.
        </p>
        <p>
          We will not sell, rent, or share Your Data with third parties except as described in our
          <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p>
          The Service, including all software, designs, text, graphics, and logos, is owned by
          Accountium and protected by Canadian and international intellectual property laws. These
          Terms do not grant you any right, title, or interest in the Service beyond the limited
          license to use it as described herein.
        </p>

        <h2>8. Availability and Uptime</h2>
        <p>
          We strive to maintain high availability of the Service but do not guarantee uninterrupted
          access. We may perform scheduled or emergency maintenance that temporarily affects
          availability. We will make reasonable efforts to notify users of planned downtime in advance.
        </p>

        <h2>9. Termination</h2>
        <h3>9.1 By you</h3>
        <p>
          You may cancel your account at any time from your account settings or by contacting us at
          <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a>. Cancellation takes effect at the end of
          your current billing period.
        </p>
        <h3>9.2 By us</h3>
        <p>
          We may suspend or terminate your account if you violate these Terms, engage in fraudulent
          activity, or for any other reason with reasonable notice. In cases of serious violations, we
          may terminate immediately without notice.
        </p>
        <p>
          Upon termination, your right to use the Service ceases. You may request an export of Your
          Data within 30 days of termination, after which we may delete it.
        </p>

        <h2>10. Disclaimers</h2>
        <p>
          The Service is provided "as is" and "as available" without warranties of any kind, express
          or implied, including but not limited to merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose,
          or non-infringement. Accountium does not warrant that the Service will be error-free or that
          any financial calculations or reports generated by the Service are accurate for tax or legal
          purposes. You are solely responsible for verifying the accuracy of your financial data.
        </p>

        <h2>11. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>
          To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, Accountium and its directors, employees,
          and affiliates shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or
          punitive damages — including loss of profits, data, or business — arising out of your use
          of or inability to use the Service, even if advised of the possibility of such damages.
        </p>
        <p>
          Our total liability to you for any claim arising from these Terms or the Service shall not
          exceed the amount you paid us in the 12 months preceding the claim.
        </p>

        <h2>12. Governing Law</h2>
        <p>
          These Terms are governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the Province of
          British Columbia and the federal laws of Canada applicable therein, without regard to conflict of law
          principles. Any disputes shall be resolved exclusively in the courts located in British Columbia, Canada.
        </p>

        <h2>13. Changes to These Terms</h2>
        <p>
          We may update these Terms from time to time. We will notify you of material changes by
          posting the updated Terms on this page and, where appropriate, by email. Your continued use
          of the Service after changes take effect constitutes your acceptance of the updated Terms.
        </p>

        <h2>14. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>
          If you have any questions about these Terms, please contact us:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Email: <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a></li>
          <li>Website: <a href="/contact">accountium.ca/contact</a></li>
        </ul>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-hero {
    padding-top: calc(var(--header-height) + var(--space-16));
  }

  .page-hero-inner {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    text-align: center;
    gap: var(--space-4);
  }

  .page-hero-inner h1 {
    font-size: var(--text-3xl);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
  }

  .page-subline {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .feat-divider {
    width: 1px;
    height: 64px;
    background: linear-gradient(to bottom, transparent, var(--color-accent), transparent);
    margin: 0 auto var(--space-4);
  }

  .prose {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: var(--space-12) var(--space-10);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-4);
  }

  .prose h2 {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    margin: var(--space-6) 0 0;
  }

  .prose h2:first-child {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .prose h3 {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    margin: var(--space-2) 0 0;
  }

  .prose p {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    max-width: none;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .prose ul {
    padding-left: var(--space-5);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-2);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .prose li {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }

  .prose a {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  .prose a:hover {
    color: var(--color-accent-hover);
  }

  .prose strong {
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .prose.glass-card {
    background: transparent;
    border: none;
    box-shadow: none;
    backdrop-filter: none;
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: none;
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .prose {
      padding: var(--space-8) var(--space-6);
    }
  }
</style>
